tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function, mild hyperchloremia, low globulin, slightly elevated total cholesterol, and low HDL cholesterol. Liver enzymes and other electrolytes are within normal limits. Findings indicate possible chronic kidney disease and increased cardiovascular risk; clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
